comments: Anunoby (TOR) makes clean contact with the ball to block Barrett's (NYK) shot prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
VanVleet (TOR) moves alongside Brunson's (NYK) path and maintains a legal guarding position as he avoids contact with Brunson's arm during the driving shot attempt.

Randle (NYK) and Anunony (TOR) briefly engage and marginal contact occurs as they jostle for potential rebounding position. Young (TOR) lands on his teammate Anunoby after contesting the shot, which causes both players to go to the ground.
Anunoby (TOR) makes contact with Randle's (NYK) lower body, which dislodges him as he attempts to secure the rebound.

VanVleet (TOR) and Randle (NYK) mutually engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs off-ball. Simultaneously, Young (TOR) is established in Randle's (NYK) path when incidental foot to foot contact occurs as they briefly come together.
Randle (NYK) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Flynn (TOR) legally contests and cleanly blocks Quickley's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Randle (NYK) is moving alongside Siakam's (TOR) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Barrett (NYK) legally contests Anunoby's (TOR) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
VanVleet (TOR) avoids contact with Randle (NYK) during the shot attempt near the rim.
Brunson (NYK) commits a take foul on VanVleet (TOR) simultaneous to any inadvertent contact to VanVleet's face by Quickley (NYK).
Siakam (TOR) brings his arm toward Brunson's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs during Brunson's drive.
Siakam (TOR) brushes Randle's (NYK) off-arm and marginal contact occurs during Randle's dunk attempt.
Randle (NYK) extends his forearm and makes contact with Siakam's (TOR) body, which affects his SQBR on the way up the court.
VanVleet (TOR) avoids contact with Brunson (NYK) during the driving shot attempt.
Hartenstein (NYK) initiates contact with Siakam's (TOR) arm, which alters his driving shot attempt.
Siakam (TOR) moves alongside Brunson's (NYK) path and legally contests the driving shot attempt.
VanVleet (TOR) and Randle (NYK) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Randle (NYK) comes together with Young (TOR) and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the rebound.
